text:
Centered slide title text on a plain light beige background:

“Cogsci/Psychology 127: Lecture 12”
“Cortical Control of Action”

Small toolbar overlay at top right with icons and labels:
blue circular button with minus sign;
“Pen”;
“highlighter”;
“Eraser”;
“Hide”;
“Close”.

Title at top, blue serif text: “Neuroprosthetics: Challenges for Human…”

Upper right overlay toolbar/icons from video player/editor:
blue circular button with white up-arrow;
small icons and labels including “GIF”, “Edit”, “Cut”, “JIM”, and a red “X”.

Two side-by-side lecture video stills centered on slide.

Left still:
robotic prosthetic arm entering from upper left, dark blue and black segments, metallic gripper/hand open above a table;
black tabletop with several pink spherical objects/balls scattered, small white and metallic objects near front edge;
vertical dark rectangular post or monitor support near center-left;
foreground lower left: pale prosthetic or mannequin-like hand/arm resting near table edge;
background right: seated man in light shirt at computer monitor, seated woman in red top to his right;
small green circular icon at bottom right of still.

Caption below left still, black serif text, underlined: “Hochberg Reaching short”

Right still:
similar robotic arm and gripper from upper left over tabletop;
dark vertical post near center;
red object attached near front/center on table apparatus;
background: same man at computer, same woman in red top seated closer to camera, face blurred;
small green circular icon at bottom right of still.

Caption below right still, black serif text, underlined: “Hochberg Movie Drinking”

Background of slide: light beige.
